[
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "heading",
    "text": "Nahum 1"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "prose",
    "text": "This is the burden against Nineveh, the book of the vision of Nahum the Elkoshite:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Yahweh is a jealous and avenging God;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "Yahweh is avenging and full of wrath."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Yahweh takes vengeance on His foes"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and reserves wrath for His enemies."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Yahweh is slow to anger"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and great in power;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Yahweh will by no means"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "leave the guilty unpunished."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "His path is in the whirlwind and storm,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and clouds are the dust beneath His feet."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "He rebukes the sea and dries it up;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "He makes all the rivers run dry."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Bashan and Carmel wither,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and the flower of Lebanon wilts."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "The mountains quake before Him,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and the hills melt away;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "the earth trembles at His presence—"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "the world and all its dwellers."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Who can withstand His indignation?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "Who can endure His burning anger?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "His wrath is poured out like fire;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "even rocks are shattered before Him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Yahweh is good,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "a stronghold in the day of distress;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "He cares for those who trust in Him."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "But with an overwhelming flood"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "He will make an end of Nineveh"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and pursue His enemies into darkness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Whatever you plot against Yahweh,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "He will bring to an end."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Affliction will not rise up"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "a second time."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "For they will be entangled as with thorns"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and consumed like the drink of a drunkard—"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "like stubble that is fully dry."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "From you, O Nineveh, comes forth"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "a plotter of evil against Yahweh,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "a counselor of wickedness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "prose",
    "text": "This is what Yahweh says:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "“Though they are allied and numerous,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "yet they will be cut down and pass away."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Though I have afflicted you, O Judah,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "I will afflict you no longer."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "For I will now break their yoke from your neck"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and tear away your shackles.”"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "prose",
    "text": "Yahweh has issued a command concerning you, O Nineveh:"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "“There will be no descendants"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "to carry on your name."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "I will cut off the carved image and cast idol"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "from the house of your gods;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "I will prepare your grave,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "for you are contemptible.”"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Look to the mountains—"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "the feet of one who brings good news,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "who proclaims peace!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Celebrate your feasts, O Judah;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "fulfill your vows."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "For the wicked will never again march through you;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 1,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "they will be utterly cut off."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "heading",
    "text": "Nahum 2"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "One who scatters advances"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "against you, O Nineveh."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Guard the fortress!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "Watch the road!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Brace yourselves!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "Summon all your strength!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "For Yahweh will restore the splendor of Jacob"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "like the splendor of Israel,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "though destroyers have laid them waste"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and ruined the branches of their vine."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "The shields of his mighty men are red;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "the valiant warriors are dressed in scarlet."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "The fittings of the chariots flash like fire"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "on the day they are prepared,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "and the spears of cypress"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "have been brandished."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "The chariots dash through the streets;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "they rush around the plazas,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "appearing like torches,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "darting about like lightning."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "He summons his nobles;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "they stumble as they advance."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "They race to its wall;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "the protective shield is set in place."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "The river gates are thrown open"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and the palace collapses."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "It is decreed that the city be exiled"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and carried away;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "her maidservants moan like doves,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and beat upon their breasts."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Nineveh has been like a pool of water"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "throughout her days,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "but now it is draining away."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "“Stop! Stop!” they cry,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "but no one turns back."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "“Plunder the silver!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "Plunder the gold!”"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "There is no end to the treasure,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "an abundance of every precious thing."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "She is emptied!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "Yes, she is desolate and laid waste!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Hearts melt, knees knock,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "bodies tremble, and every face grows pale!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Where is the lions’ lair"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "or the feeding ground of the young lions,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "where the lion and lioness prowled with their cubs,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "with nothing to frighten them away?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "The lion mauled enough for its cubs"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and strangled prey for the lioness."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "It filled its dens with the kill,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and its lairs with mauled prey."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "“Behold, I am against you,”"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "declares Yahweh of Hosts."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "“I will send your chariots up in smoke,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and the sword will devour your young lions."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "I will cut off your prey from the earth,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and the voices of your messengers"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 2,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "will no longer be heard.”"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "heading",
    "text": "Nahum 3"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Woe to the city of blood,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "full of lies,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "full of plunder,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "never without prey."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "The crack of the whip,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "the rumble of the wheel,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "galloping horse"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and bounding chariot!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Charging horseman,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "flashing sword,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "shining spear;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "heaps of slain,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "mounds of corpses,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "dead bodies without end—"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "they stumble over their dead—"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "because of the many harlotries of the harlot,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "the seductive mistress of sorcery,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "who betrays nations by her prostitution"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and clans by her witchcraft."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "“Behold, I am against you,”"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "declares Yahweh of Hosts."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "“I will lift your skirts over your face."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "I will show your nakedness to the nations"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and your shame to the kingdoms."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "I will pelt you with filth"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and treat you with contempt;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "I will make a spectacle of you."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Then all who see you"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "will recoil from you and say,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "‘Nineveh is devastated;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "who will grieve for her?’"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Where can I find"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "comforters for you?”"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Are you better than Thebes,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "stationed by the Nile with water around her,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "whose rampart was the sea,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "whose wall was the water?"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Cush and Egypt were her boundless strength;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "Put and Libya were her allies."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Yet she became an exile;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "she went into captivity."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Her infants were dashed to pieces"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "at the head of every street."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "They cast lots for her dignitaries,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and all her nobles were bound in chains."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "You too will become drunk;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "you will go into hiding"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and seek refuge from the enemy."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "All your fortresses are fig trees"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "with the first ripe figs;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "when shaken, they fall"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "into the mouth of the eater!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Look at your troops—"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "they are like your women!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "The gates of your land"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "are wide open to your enemies;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "fire consumes their bars."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Draw your water for the siege;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "strengthen your fortresses."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Work the clay and tread the mortar;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "repair the brick kiln!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "There the fire will devour you;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "the sword will cut you down"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and consume you like a young locust."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Make yourself many like the young locust;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "make yourself many like the swarming locust!"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "You have multiplied your merchants"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "more than the stars of the sky."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "The young locust strips the land"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and flies away."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Your guards are like the swarming locust,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and your scribes like clouds of locusts"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "that settle on the walls on a cold day."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "When the sun rises, they fly away,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "and no one knows where."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "O king of Assyria, your shepherds slumber;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "your officers sleep."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "Your people are scattered on the mountains"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "with no one to gather them."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "There is no healing for your injury;"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "your wound is severe."
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "All who hear the news of you"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "applaud your downfall,"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l1",
    "text": "for who has not experienced"
  },
  {
    "book": "Nahum",
    "chapter": 3,
    "type": "poetry_l2",
    "text": "your constant cruelty?"
  }
]